description: From Latin infuscatus, past participle of infuscare; prefix in- (“in”) + fuscare (“to make dark”), from fuscus (“dark”).

adjectives.description: infuscate (comparative more infuscate, superlative most infuscate)

verbs.description: infuscate (third-person singular simple present infuscates, present participle infuscating, simple past and past participle infuscated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To darken; to make black or obscure.
